\vec k=\vec i \times \vec j
\vec i=(1,0,0), \vec j = (0,1,0)
\vec k = (0,0,1)
(0,0,1) = (1,0,0) \times (0,1,0)
\vec{a} \times \vec{b} = \left|\begin{matrix} \hat \imath & \hat \jmath & \hat k \\ a_x & a_y & a_z \\ b_x & b_y & b_z\end{matrix}\right|
\hat \imath = 1\hat \imath + 0 \hat \jmath + 0 \hat k
\hat \jmath = 0\hat \imath + 1 \hat \jmath + 0 \hat k
\vec{a} = \hat \imath
\vec{b} = \hat \jmath
\hat{\imath} \times \hat{\jmath} = \left|\begin{matrix} \hat \imath & \hat \jmath & \hat k \\ 1 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 1 & 0\end{matrix}\right|
